          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Gamma rays of 6.14, 6.91 and 7.12 MeV produced by the",
                " F-19(p,a+g)O-16 reaction were used to  induce  heavy",
                " element fission.  The photofission cross sections of",
                " Th-232,  U-238,236,235,234,233,  and Np-237 for 6.14",
                " and  7.0  MeV average gamma ray energy (a mixture of",
                " 6.91 and 7.12 MeV gamma rays) were measured."
              ]
            }
          ],
